`inspect.stack()` is slow because it materializes all stack frames into a list - nearly 1ms on my machine. Here, I think we really only care about the function name at frame N-5, right? If so, can we replace this with:

```py
frame = inspect.currentframe()
for _ in range(5):
    try:
        frame = frame.f_back
    except AttributeError:
        break
else:
    is_aggregate = 'aggregate' in frame.function
del frame

if is_aggregate:
    ...
```

If you agree but don't have time, I'm happy to open up a PR myself.
